<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why Container Gardening Is Harder in Cool Climates</h2>

  <p>
    Containers change how plants grow:
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>less soil volume limits root development</li>
    <li>temperature swings are more extreme</li>
    <li>watering and nutrients fluctuate more quickly</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    In cool climates, you add:
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>slower early growth</li>
    <li>reduced heat accumulation</li>
    <li>higher risk of incomplete maturity</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Together, this means many standard varieties struggle — even if they are labeled “container-friendly.”
  </p>
</section>

